Battlefield markers and unit drawer markers reference list

When a new unit is added, make sure to update this list and use it as a reference.

Make sure the unit name is unique, the internal name is unique, the string fragment is unique and that possible conflicts are avoided (e.g. Rogue/Flying Rogue)

In some cases the internal name must be used, such as alliespaladin instead of paladin, observe the pattern on each file to figure out which name is being used
The API request getUserUnits on the Network tab of devtools can provide the internal name.

The files that need to be edited with the new units information are:

unit_icons.txt
content_script.js
quest_handler.js (Apart from the array, if the unit name is not unique [e.g Rogue/Flying Rogue] the ruleset must be edited as well to avoid conflicts)
units_handler.js
quick_set.js?
units.html
